sections.content:
“action” means a civil proceeding commenced by writ or in such
other manner as may be prescribed by rules of court and includes
a  counterclaim;

“compulsory  licence”  means  the  authorization  to  perform  in
Malaysia, without the agreement of the right holder of the protected
layout-design,  any  act  referred  to  in  section  9;

“creator”,  in  relation  to  a  computer-aided  design  of  a  layout-
design,  means  the  person  who  made  the  arrangements  for  the
creation  of  the  layout-design;

“material  form”,  in  relation  to  a  layout-design,  includes  any
form  of  storage  (whether  visible  or  not)  from  which  the  layout-
design, or a substantial part of the layout-design, can be reproduced;

“qualifying country” means a country or territory that is a Member
to the World Trade Organization Agreement and includes a country
or  territory  designated  under  section  4;

(a) if  the  layout-design  is  not  created  in  pursuance  of  a
commission or in the course of employment, the creator
of  the  layout-design  is  the  right  holder;

(a) if  the  reproduction  is  of  any  part  of  a  protected  layout-
design  that  does  not  comply  with  the  requirement  of
originality  referred  to  in  subsection  5(1);

(e) to  do  any  of  the  acts  referred  to  in  section  9  in  respect
of  the  different  layout-design  referred  to  in  paragraph
(d);

(b) an  unauthorized  integrated  circuit,  being  an  integrated
circuit in which the protected layout-design is incorporated;
or

(i) who swears an affidavit under subsection (1) that
is scandalous, irrelevant or otherwise oppressive;
or

(C) there  is  no  infringement  of  the  plaintiff’s
rights as a right holder of a protected layout-
design;

(b) prescribing the fees and charges payable under this Act
and  the  manner  for  collecting  and  disbursing  such  fees
and  charges;
